@@gBrine-Stained Passage of the Reach@@N~
Brine-Stained Passage of the Reach reads like a record etched into architecture rather than a place designed all at once.  Warden paint marks still divide traffic channels even where the original paving has failed.  Canvas shade snaps in the wind while clerks call out loads and witnesses answer by rote.  Tariff stones near the lane edge show three generations of overwritten conversion notes.  From here, movement commits south with little opportunity to hedge the decision.
~
